{"type":"message","id":"1c5354ee","parentId":"cddd059a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:28:50.949Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9seavp0d1ygf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis âœ…\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis âœ… (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- Î» parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse âœ…\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune Î» empirically (start: Î»=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure â€\" compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) â€\" test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** â€\" session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **Î» encodes both** â€\" decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** â€\" Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** â€\" session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless â€\" each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\nPending:\n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n\n\nRecent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-23 112738.md\n\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n`\nold_text: [exact text to find - or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n`\n\"@\n\n = \"\"\nif (sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0) {\n     = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n     = @{\n        model = MiniMax-M2.7\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = })\n    }\n     = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes(( | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5 -Compress))\n     = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers  -Body  -TimeoutSec 60\n    try {\n         = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers  -Body  -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: \"\n         = .choices\n         = \n        if ( -ne  -and .Count -gt 0) {  = [0] }\n        if ( -ne ) {\n             = .message.content\n            if ( -eq ) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: \"\n                 = \"\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content length: 0\"\n                 = \n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"[DEBUG] No choices. Full resp: \"\n             = \"No choices: \"\n        }\n    } catch {\n         = \"LLM call failed: \"\n    }\n} else {\n     = \"[No LLM API key]\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block â€” extract old_text, new_text (multiline), and file from the block\n = False\n = .IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ( -ge 0) {\n     = .Substring()\n    # Remove ALL code fences (replace each fence pair with placeholder, repeat until stable)\n     = \"\"\n    while ( -ne ) {  = ;  =  -replace '(?s)`.*?`', \"\n[CODE_BLOCK]\n\" }\n    # Extract fields\n     = [regex]::Match(, 'old_text:\\s*(.+)')\n     = [regex]::Match(, 'file:\\s*(.+)')\n     = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n     = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    # new_text: between \"new_text:\" line and \"file:\" line (after fence removal)\n     = \"\"\n    if ( -and ) {\n         = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)new_text:\\s*\\n(.+?)\\s*\\n\\s*file:', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n        if (.Success) {  = .Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\n    }\n    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not ) {\n         = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if (.Success) {\n             = .Groups[1].Value\n            # Match \"Create path/file.md\" or \"Edit path/file.md\" with or without backticks\n             = [regex]::Match(, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:`([^`]+)`|([^\\s]+))')\n            if (.Success) {\n                 = if (.Groups[2].Value) { .Groups[2].Value } else { .Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] \"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    if ( -and  -and ) {\n        if ( -eq \"(new file)\") {\n             = \"\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n\"\n        } else {\n             = \"\n---\n\n---\n\"\n        }\n         = Join-Path C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed \"2026-03-23 112845.mutation\"\n         | Out-File -FilePath  -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] \"\n         = True\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old_text= file= new_text_len=0\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n    = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: 2026-03-23 112845\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 11:28:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279730947}}
